Swan upping
When they do this kind of thing they need calmer waters
they have to handle them very carefully They use small Boats people think this is very cruel to catch them and put stamp on their wings, in this picture there is a man carrying one out of the Boat its Wings are tied so that it can not break the man's arms, the swans are delicate things

Poem
one day the sun was out and up the stairs I went
My mother in a temper, I spent my day in bed
for fear of my mother I daren't go near
For fear I didn't get to see the sun,
There she lays So quietly there Waiting for the day People weeping waiting Sighing all the days Their hearts are weeping Crying so Hearts beating so rapidly

